            "name": "Line of Sight",
            "ownership": {
                "dOcXwrUs2VunZl0y": 3,
                "default": -1
            },
            "sort": 2,
            "src": null,
            "system": {},
            "text": {
                "content": "<p>Line of Sight refers to a creature being able to see something within their field of view. If a PC watches a creature run behind a castle wall, that creature is no longer in the PC\u2019s Line of Sight.</p><p>On a grid map, this would mean that you can draw a straight line from any one corner of the Space that you\u2019re on, to any one corner of a Space that the other creature is on. If you can see a creature but they\u2019re partially behind something (a wall, another creature, etc.), then they have <strong>Cover </strong>(see below).</p>",
                "format": 1
            },
            "title": {
                "level": 1,
                "show": true
            },
            "type": "text",
            "video": {
                "controls": true,
                "volume": 0.5
            }
        },
        {
            "_id": "d35f996aa1711f8f",
            "_key": "!journal.pages!7374b83f0432972a.d35f996aa1711f8f",
            "_stats": {
                "compodiumSource": null,
                "coreVersion": "12.327",
                "createdTime": 1721459260.734043,
                "duplicateSource": null,
                "lastModifiedBy": "dOcXwrUs2VunZl0y",
                "modifiedTime": 1721459260.734043,
                "systemId": "dc20rpg",
                "systemVersion": "0.8.0"
            },
            "flags": {},
            "image": {},
            "name": "Cover",
            "ownership": {
                "dOcXwrUs2VunZl0y": 3,
                "default": -1
            },
            "sort": 3,
            "src": null,
            "system": {},
            "text": {
                "content": "<p><strong><em>1/2 Cover: </em></strong>Creatures have a <strong>-2 </strong>penalty on Attack Checks and Spell Checks against a target\u2019s PD while the target is behind 1/2 Cover.</p><p>A creature benefits from 1/2 Cover when it\u2019s hiding behind a chair, a small table, or another creature of the same size or larger.</p><p><strong><em>3/4 Cover: </em></strong>Creatures have a <strong>-5 </strong>penalty on Attack Checks and Spell Checks against a target\u2019s PD while the target is behind 3/4 Cover.</p><p>A creature benefits from 3/4 Cover when it\u2019s hiding behind a large piece of furniture, it\u2019s hiding behind a creature 2 or more sizes larger than it, or if it\u2019s partially covered by a wall.</p><p><strong><em>Full Cover: </em></strong>Creatures can\u2019t make Attack Checks or Spell Checks against a target\u2019s PD while the target is behind Full Cover.</p><p>A creature benefits from Full Cover when it\u2019s completely behind an object that\u2019s larger than them.</p>",
                "format": 1
            },
            "title": {
                "level": 2,
                "show": true
            },
            "type": "text",
            "video": {
                "controls": true,
                "volume": 0.5
            }
        },
        {
            "_id": "c75251402280e179",
            "_key": "!journal.pages!7374b83f0432972a.c75251402280e179",
            "_stats": {
                "compodiumSource": null,
                "coreVersion": "12.327",
                "createdTime": 1721459260.734043,
                "duplicateSource": null,
                "lastModifiedBy": "dOcXwrUs2VunZl0y",
                "modifiedTime": 1721459260.734043,
                "systemId": "dc20rpg",
                "systemVersion": "0.8.0"
