        {
            "_id": "c07583a0bdc57492",
            "_key": "!journal.pages!7374b83f0432972a.c07583a0bdc57492",
            "_stats": {
                "compodiumSource": null,
                "coreVersion": "12.327",
                "createdTime": 1721459260.734043,
                "duplicateSource": null,
                "lastModifiedBy": "dOcXwrUs2VunZl0y",
                "modifiedTime": 1721459260.734043,
                "systemId": "dc20rpg",
                "systemVersion": "0.8.0"
            },
            "flags": {},
            "image": {},
            "name": "Darkvision",
            "ownership": {
                "dOcXwrUs2VunZl0y": 3,
                "default": -1
            },
            "sort": 11,
            "src": null,
            "system": {},
            "text": {
                "content": "<p>Creatures with Darkvision have the ability to see in Dim Light and Darkness out to a specified range. A creature with Darkvision can see areas of Dim Light within the specified range as if it were Bright Light, and see areas of Darkness within the specified range as if it were Dim Light. A creature can\u2019t discern color using their Darkvision, only shades of gray.</p><div class=\"book-block book-block-example>A creature with Darkvision 10 can see up to 10 Spaces in Dim Light as if it were Bright Light, and up to 10 Spaces in Darkness as if it were Dim Light.</div>",
                "format": 1
            },
            "title": {
                "level": 2,
                "show": true
            },
            "type": "text",
            "video": {
                "controls": true,
                "volume": 0.5
            }
        },
        {
            "_id": "8c1de93cb3b1cc00",
            "_key": "!journal.pages!7374b83f0432972a.8c1de93cb3b1cc00",
            "_stats": {
                "compodiumSource": null,
                "coreVersion": "12.327",
                "createdTime": 1721459260.734043,
                "duplicateSource": null,
                "lastModifiedBy": "dOcXwrUs2VunZl0y",
                "modifiedTime": 1721459260.734043,
                "systemId": "dc20rpg",
                "systemVersion": "0.8.0"
            },
            "flags": {},
            "image": {},
            "name": "Tremorsense",
            "ownership": {
                "dOcXwrUs2VunZl0y": 3,
                "default": -1
            },
            "sort": 12,
            "src": null,
            "system": {},
            "text": {
                "content": "<p>Creatures with Tremorsense can sense vibrations in the ground within a specified range, allowing them to automatically pinpoint the location of anything that\u2019s in contact with the same surface, including through Cover and Concealment.</p><p>Creatures with Tremorsense and a Swim Speed can also pinpoint the location of creatures moving through water within the specified range.</p>",
                "format": 1
            },
            "title": {
                "level": 2,
                "show": true
            },
            "type": "text",
            "video": {
                "controls": true,
                "volume": 0.5
            }
        },
        {
            "_id": "d8fae46c6a6f91c0",
            "_key": "!journal.pages!7374b83f0432972a.d8fae46c6a6f91c0",
            "_stats": {
                "compodiumSource": null,
                "coreVersion": "12.327",
                "createdTime": 1721459260.734043,
                "duplicateSource": null,
                "lastModifiedBy": "dOcXwrUs2VunZl0y",
                "modifiedTime": 1721459260.734043,
                "systemId": "dc20rpg",
                "systemVersion": "0.8.0"
            },
            "flags": {},
            "image": {},
            "name": "Blindsight",
            "ownership": {
                "dOcXwrUs2VunZl0y": 3,
                "default": -1
            },
            "sort": 13,
            "src": null,
            "system": {},
            "text": {
                "content": "<p>Creatures with Blindsight have the ability to see things within a specified range without the use of eyes. Creatures without eyes or that can see using echolocation are able to see things using Blindsight. A creature with Blindsight can see things that are <strong>Invisible</strong>, is immune to being Blinded, and can see unimpeded by<strong> Concealment</strong>. Blindsight doesn\u2019t grant a creature the ability to see behind<strong> Cover</strong>.</p><div class=\"book-block book-block-example>A creature with Blindsight 5 can see up to 5 Spaces in any direction as if they could see normally. This includes Invisible creatures within range and creatures that are Partially or Fully Concealed within range that aren\u2019t behind Cover.</div>",
                "format": 1
            },
            "title": {
                "level": 2,
                "show": true
            },
            "type": "text",
            "video": {
                "controls": true,
                "volume": 0.5
            }
        },
        {
            "_id": "ab56aa2efa6b60fd",
            "_key": "!journal.pages!7374b83f0432972a.ab56aa2efa6b60fd",
            "_stats": {
                "compodiumSource": null,
                "coreVersion": "12.327",
                "createdTime": 1721459260.734043,
                "duplicateSource": null,
                "lastModifiedBy": "dOcXwrUs2VunZl0y",
                "modifiedTime": 1721459260.734043,
                "systemId": "dc20rpg",
                "systemVersion": "0.8.0"
            },
            "flags": {},
            "image": {},
            "name": "Truesight",
            "ownership": {
                "dOcXwrUs2VunZl0y": 3,
                "default": -1
            },
            "sort": 14,
            "src": null,
            "system": {},
            "text": {
                "content": "<p>Creatures with Truesight have the ability to see things that are normally imperceptible out to a specified range. They can see through normal and Magical Darkness, see into the Ethereal Plane from the Material Plane (and vice versa), see things that are Invisible, automatically see through illusions, and can perceive the true form of a Shapechanger or creature that\u2019s transformed by magic.</p><div class=\"book-block book-block-example>A creature with Truesight 10 can see up to 10 Spaces in Darkness normally, see creatures within range that are Invisible or on the Ethereal Plane, and see the true form of any creature that is shapeshifted.</div>",
                "format": 1
            },
            "title": {
                "level": 2,
